BRIEFLY 
Development Bank Vote Causes Controversy: The Netherlands and Belgium have 
threatened to contest the choice of French presidential adviser Jacques Attali 
as head of the new European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, designed 
to revive the economies of Eastern Europe, and the choice of London as its 
headquarters. Attali won over a Dutch rival and London over the Dutch city of 
Amsterdam. The treaty establishing the bank is to be signed in Paris on May 29. 
